                  <interp inst="t17980418-38-crimeloc196" type="placeName" value="No. 137, St. Martin's-lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17980418-38-crimeloc196" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17980418-38-off194 t17980418-38-crimeloc196"></join>: On the 1st of March the prisoner came into my shop under pretence of buying a pair of small cloaths, I gave him several pair to try, he tried them; I asked him seven shillings for a pair, and he offered me six; I told him I could not take less. I missed a pair of small cloaths as soon as he was gone; I fetched him back again, and found this pair inside of his; these are them, they have my private mark upon them.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by Mr. Alley. Q. Are they velveteen breeches? - A.They are.</p>
               <p>Q. Did not you stand by him while he tried them on? - A. No.</p>
               <p>The prisoner did not say any thing in his defence, but called two witnesses, who gave him a good character.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17980418-38-verdict197" type="verdictDescription">
